\f0\fs24 \cf0 PRD: DataEvol \'97 Self-Evolving Data Collection, Labeling, Benchmark, and Experiment Pipeline\
1. Product Name\
DataEvol\
Working subtitle:\
A self-evolving data engine for agent traces, router decisions, scientific workflows, benchmarks, and training candidates.\
2. Core Goal\
DataEvol is a standalone repo/service that continuously improves the Fractal/BioLatent ecosystem by collecting traces, labeling outcomes, compressing useful failures, generating synthetic variants, building benchmarks, and running controlled micro-experiments before any improvement is promoted.\
It should not be inside Coordinate, BioLatent, or the Router API.\
Those systems should call DataEvol through an API.\
coordinate/\
  terminal spawning, worker execution, task graph\
\
fractal-router-api/\
  worker/model routing and assignment\
\
biolatent/\
  scientific workflows, protocols, verification\
\
dataevol/\
  trace ingestion, labeling, scoring, synthetic data, benchmarks, experiments, promotion gates\
3. One-Sentence Vision\
DataEvol is the Datology-style data engine for Fractal: it turns raw agent traces, failures, corrections, verifier results, and user workflows into better datasets, better benchmarks, better prompts, better router policies, and better local models \'97 but only promotes changes after controlled experiments show measurable improvement.\
4. Main Principle\
DataEvol must never blindly self-modify production behavior.\
Every proposed improvement must go through:\
observe\
  -> label\
  -> score\
  -> compress\
  -> generate idea\
  -> create Idea PRD\
  -> run sandbox experiment\
  -> compare against baseline\
  -> verify no regression\
  -> promote or reject\
No benchmark improvement, no promotion.\
No regression check, no promotion.\
No rollback path, no promotion.\
5. What DataEvol Improves\
DataEvol can improve:\
router decisions\
worker assignment\
model mix policy\
prompt packs\
task decomposition\
trace compression\
duplicate detection\
verifier/critic prompts\
benchmark suites\
synthetic data generation\
local router datasets\
local evaluator datasets\
local compressor datasets\
negative-example handling\
cost/latency efficiency\
scientific workflow quality\
coding-agent workflows\
OpenRouter free/cheap model ranking\
6. What DataEvol Does Not Do\
DataEvol does not:\
execute user tasks directly\
spawn terminal workers\
replace Coordinate\
replace BioLatent\
replace the Fractal Router API\
make final scientific claims\
auto-push changes to production\
train on private user data without opt-in\
store raw sensitive data when a compact/redacted trace is sufficient\
