12. Trace Outcome Labels\
Every trace should be labeled with outcome:\
accepted\
rejected\
failed_tests\
failed_verification\
hallucinated\
duplicated\
too_expensive\
too_slow\
rescued_by_stronger_model\
useful_negative_example\
good_training_candidate\
unsafe_or_policy_blocked\
inconclusive\
13. Failure Taxonomy\
Wrong answers are valuable, but they must be stored as negative/evaluator data, not as good-answer data.\
Failure types:\
wrong_reasoning\
wrong_tool\
bad_router_assignment\
hallucinated_citation\
fabricated_data\
failed_code_tests\
bad_scientific_claim\
weak_evidence\
missed_dependency\
duplicated_work\
overused_frontier_model\
underused_local_model\
context_loss\
format_failure\
unsafe_output\
14. Retention Policy\
Not all data should be kept at full size.\
Accepted high-value trace:\
  keep full trace + compressed version\
\
Wrong but informative trace:\
  keep compressed trace + failure label + corrected trace link\
\
Low-value repeated junk:\
  keep metadata only or discard after summary\
\
Sensitive/private trace:\
  redact or keep local-only according to user setting\
15. Privacy Modes\
DataEvol must support three modes:\
private-local-only\
shared-anonymous-learning\
public-benchmark-contribution\
Default:\
private-local-only\
Rules:\
Raw user data stays local unless user opts in.\
Sensitive data is redacted before dataset export.\
Training candidates must carry privacy status.\
Public benchmarks cannot include private user content.\
User can delete run data.\
User can disable synthetic generation on private traces.\
Command:\
dataevol privacy set private-local-only\
