19. Idea PRD Format\
Every proposed improvement must become an Idea PRD before experiments run.\
# Idea PRD: <title>\
\
## Observation\
What happened?\
\
## Hypothesis\
What change might improve the system?\
\
## Affected Component\
router | prompt | dataset | benchmark | verifier | critic | compressor | local_model | model_mix\
\
## Baseline\
Current behavior.\
\
## Variant\
Proposed new behavior.\
\
## Benchmark\
Frozen benchmark to test against.\
\
## Primary Metric\
The metric that must improve.\
\
## Non-Regression Metrics\
Metrics that must not get worse.\
\
## Safety Checks\
What must remain safe?\
\
## Reproducibility Requirement\
How many repeated runs must pass?\
\
## Rollback Plan\
How to undo this change.\
\
## Promotion Rule\
Exact condition for promotion.\
\
## Rejection Rule\
Exact condition for rejection.\
20. Promotion Gate\
A candidate change can only be promoted if:\
primary metric improves\
AND no critical regression occurs\
AND safety score does not decline\
AND verification pass rate does not decline\
AND result reproduces across at least 2 runs\
AND rollback snapshot exists\
Example promotion rules:\
Router policy improvement:\
  cost_per_verified_task decreases by >= 20%\
  correctness decreases by <= 0%\
  safety regressions = 0\
\
Prompt improvement:\
  task success improves by >= 5%\
  hallucination rate does not increase\
  average cost does not increase by more than 10%\
\
Compressor improvement:\
  token count decreases by >= 40%\
  key-fact retention >= 95%\
  failure labels preserved\
21. MVP Scope\
The MVP should prove one full loop:\
Coordinate run traces\
  -> DataEvol ingest\
  -> label traces\
  -> score traces\
  -> compress wrong traces\
  -> build router dataset\
  -> generate one router-policy Idea PRD\
  -> run control-vs-variant benchmark\
  -> promote or reject with report\
MVP does not need:\
distributed training\
large fine-tunes\
cloud dashboard\
full synthetic pretraining corpus\
automatic production deployment\
multi-tenant SaaS\
