26. MVP Definition of Done\
MVP is complete when:\
- [x] DataEvol is a separate repo.\
- [x] Coordinate or a mocked Coordinate run can send traces to DataEvol.\
- [x] DataEvol ingests traces into SQLite.\
- [x] Traces are validated, normalized, redacted, and deduped.\
- [x] Traces are labeled by outcome and failure type.\
- [x] Traces are scored for quality, correctness, cost, latency, safety, and training value.\
- [x] Wrong traces are compressed into useful negative examples.\
- [x] DataEvol exports at least one router dataset.\
- [x] DataEvol builds at least one frozen benchmark.\
- [x] Evolver Agent detects at least one learning opportunity.\
- [x] DataEvol generates one Idea PRD.\
- [x] DataEvol runs a control-vs-variant sandbox experiment.\
- [x] DataEvol promotes only if metrics improve and no regression is found.\
- [x] Failed ideas are rejected and archived as negative evidence.\
- [x] Privacy mode defaults to private-local-only.\
27. First Real MVP Experiment\
The first experiment should be simple:\
Hypothesis\
Low-risk literature/documentation tasks can be routed to OpenRouter free models instead of Claude/Codex without reducing verification pass rate.\
Baseline\
Current router policy.\
Variant\
Updated router policy sends low-risk literature/documentation tasks to OpenRouter free models first.\
Benchmark\
50 prior low-risk documentation/literature tasks.\
Primary Metric\
Cost per verified task.\
Non-Regression Metrics\
verification pass rate\
human correction rate\
hallucination rate\
task completion rate\
Promotion Rule\
Promote if:\
cost_per_verified_task decreases by >= 30%\
AND verification_pass_rate does not decrease\
AND hallucination_rate does not increase\
AND result reproduces across 2 runs\
Rollback\
Restore previous router policy version.\
28. Final Long-Term Loop\
Every run\
  -> traces\
  -> labels\
  -> scores\
  -> compressed positives/negatives\
  -> datasets\
  -> benchmarks\
  -> Idea PRDs\
  -> experiments\
  -> validated improvements\
  -> better router/prompts/verifiers/local models\
  -> next run improves\
29. Key Insight\
The goal is not to save every trace forever.\
The goal is to turn every run into structured learning:\
good answer\
  -> positive training data\
\
wrong answer\
  -> negative/verifier data\
\
expensive success\
  -> router optimization data\
\
repeated failure\
  -> benchmark or prompt improvement data\
\
human correction\
  -> high-value supervised data\
\
verification failure\
  -> critic/verifier training data\
DataEvol is the memory and scientific improvement engine for the entire Fractal ecosystem.\
